N2  - In the ever-changing environment of modern naval operations, precise evaluation of the suitability of ship equipment is crucial for formulating effective operational decisions. However, due to the complexity of the operational environment and the variability of the systems themselves, traditional evaluation methods are no longer sufficient to meet modern demands. To address this issue, this paper proposes a multi-agent based simulation verification method for ship equipment suitability. Utilizing the AnyLogic simulation platform, this method constructs an evaluation model that simulates the constituent elements of ship equipment and their dynamic behaviors, enabling in-depth analysis of factors affecting the operational adaptability of ship equipment. The model developed in this study not only provides quantitative and qualitative assessments of the suitability of ship equipment but also offers robust scientific support for the formulation and optimization of operational strategies. It boasts high accuracy and comprehensiveness, better adapting to the complexities of modern naval operations. © 2024 IEEE.
