N2  - Professionals deal with a lot of physical and mental stress in today's fast paced work environments, which frequently results in long-term health problems, decreased productivity, and financial difficulties. This project presents a smart wellness solution for office workers that leverages wearable technology to track activity levels and health metrics utilizing an MLP algorithm powered by machine intelligence and IoT based alert notification using GSM. To encourage healthier habits, the system actively monitors posture, recognizes weariness, and recommends timely breaks. The incorporation of a Galvanic Skin Response (GSR) sensor into an Internet of Things framework to gauge stress and dehydration levels is a crucial component. The gadget uses integrated AI algorithms to spot anomalous trends in daily routines or wellness metrics, warning users to take preventative action for better health management. The method seeks to improve general well-being and promote healthier habits to reduce stress-related risks, increase productivity, and cultivate a more positive and sustainable work environment. © 2025 IEEE.
