N2  - The smart monitoring system is the advanced technique that can make use of deep learning in improving home safety and security. This paper introduces a novel smart monitoring system that brings tremendous improvements in home safety and security with cutting-edge deep learning techniques, and particularly using Convolutional Neural Network with ResN et-50 algorithm. The system is identifying the behaviors and classifying these in real time through feeds of live video from strategically situated cameras. Advanced systems processing data through a number of modules, beginning with all the loading and preprocessing right up to the retrieval of features that would be basically essential, such as motion pattern and object detection. Such features develop a base for the deep learning model's training against normal activities and potential violations of security. It carries robust fail-safe techniques with cloud backup and offline alert mechanisms so that it keeps performing even when connectivity is lost at times. Finally, sound data encryption and secure means of log-in prevent penetration. This continuous learning mechanism within the system helps it adjust itself to new data inputs and keeps improving situational awareness as well as providing proactive defense against emergencies or security breaches. This system therefore provides an innovative, resilient solution to modern challenges in home security. © 2025 IEEE.
