N2  - The presented work is devoted to multi-agent modeling of computer operator behavior. The use of multi-agent architecture makes it possible not only to emulate various behavioral strategies, but also to systematically study the influence of individual factors related to user behavior on the results of human-machine interaction. The tools developed on the basis of computer operator models can be used both for testing user interfaces (UX testing) and for analyzing risks associated with the human factor in mission-critical applications. The purpose of this work is to create a software prototype for simulating human-machine interaction, taking into account the operator's behavioral profile and conducting experiments aimed at studying the characteristics of various types of operators. The results obtained make it possible to formalize user profiles and offer recommendations for adapting interfaces to their features. © 2025 IEEE.
