N2  - With the continuous expansion of large public spaces in urban areas, fire evacuation procedures are encountering significant challenges. This paper presents a comprehensive framework called F-MAP that combines fire prediction, multi-agent model, and the path planning algorithm to enhance evacuation efficiency during fire incidents. F-MAP utilizes temperature and smoke prediction data as the base of dynamic obstacles. And by considering flow density, an improved A∗ algorithm is employed to optimize the path planning for the multi agent system. Experimental results demonstrate that F-MAP outperforms existing methods in non-fire conditions. In fire conditions, F-MAP integrates related factors to provide safer evacuation routes. Through the consideration of agents' behavior, F-MAP minimizes path overlap, resulting in enhanced evacuation efficiency and improved personnel survival rates. © 2024 IEEE.
