N2  - Accompanied by an increase in the level of mathematical intelligence, accounting information security is facing more and more challenges, including information leakage, data tampering and other issues. Therefore, it is imperative to strengthen accounting information security control. Firstly, through literature review and case analysis, this paper summarizes the challenges and problems faced by accounting information security under the background of digital intelligence. Secondly, based on the multi-agent evolutionary game theory, this paper analyzes the strategy selection rules of different subjects in accounting information security control, constructs the multi-agent strategy game matrix, and calculates the replication dynamic equation. Finally, combined with practical investigation, different scenarios are set up to carry out evolutionary analysis of the multi-agent strategy selection behavior under different circumstances. The results of this paper have certain theoretical and practical value for promoting the improvement of accounting information security control theory and practice. © 2024 ACM.
