N2  - The mutually beneficial and symbiotic development of multi-agent digital innovation platforms holds significant practical importance for enhancing the new advantages of China's platform economy and achieving high-quality development in platform innovation. This study integrates theories such as the digital economy and symbiosis theory, employing a dynamic symbiotic evolution model to analyze the intrinsic mechanisms of symbiotic evolution in innovation behaviors among platform enterprises, with a focus on the openness of innovation agents. It explores the symbiotic evolution mechanisms of innovation under three models: complementary enterprise-led, digital innovation platform-led, and government-guided and platform-led, supplemented by empirical analysis and numerical simulations. The findings reveal: (1) In complementary enterprise-led innovation symbiosis, high-niche and low-niche complementors struggle to form a mutually beneficial symbiotic relationship for innovation cooperation under asymmetric openness levels; (2) In digital innovation platform-led symbiotic evolution, the cross-effect between platform openness and heterogeneity is the key factor in forming multi-agent mutually beneficial symbiotic relationships; (3) Government-guided and platform-led innovation symbiosis shows that the exogenous impetus provided by the government for digital innovation platforms helps multi-agent platforms achieve a mutually beneficial model of innovation cooperation. This study offers optimization directions for addressing the multi-agent symbiosis challenges in digital innovation platforms. © Conference Proceedings of the 13th International Symposium on Project Management, ISPM 2025.
