N2  - This paper investigates a class of first-order discrete-time multi-agent systems (MASs) that maintain (ϵ, δ)- differentially private. Firstly, we introduce function-generated noise to agents to obscure information, safeguarding the privacy of agents against adversaries' attacks. Secondly, Conditions for achieving mean-square consensus of the MASs in the presence of added noise are explored, ensuring convergence of agents' states to the mean of initial states. Thirdly, (ϵ, δ)-differential privacy for the MASs is achieved by optimizing or adjusting parameters of the Gaussian mechanism. Finally, the validation of the proposed methods is demonstrated through numerical simulations. © 2024 IEEE.
