N2  - The reliability of urban rail transit signal system is crucial to urban transportation, and its simulation test scheduling efficiency affects the safety and stability of the system. This paper proposes an intelligent scheduling algorithm based on multi-agent collaboration and dynamic priority (MAC-DP Scheduler). By building a multi-agent model to simulate tasks and resources, the dynamic priority mechanism is used to adjust the task scheduling order in real time. Experiments are carried out in a simulated urban rail transit signal system test environment, and compared with traditional fixed priority scheduling algorithms and scheduling algorithms based on average task execution time. The results show that in scenarios with a large number of tasks and limited resources, the MACDP Scheduler algorithm shortens the average task completion time by 30 %, improves resource utilization by 25 %, and reduces the proportion of tasks missing deadlines by 40 %. In different experimental scenarios, the algorithm shows good performance advantages, effectively improves the efficiency and reliability of simulation test scheduling, and provides a new solution for the test optimization of urban rail transit signal system. © 2025 IEEE.
