N2  - This paper presents a new multi-agent planning framework under temporal logic constraints, which extends the Conflict-Based Search (CBS) approach to handle linear temporal logic (LTL) tasks. First, an algorithm is developed that integrates the Bottleneck Assignment Problem (BAP) algorithm to optimize task allocation. By verifying and adjusting task sequences based on relaxed partially ordered set structures, the proposed method ensures feasible and optimal plans. Experiments demonstrate that our algorithm can effectively minimize the total task completion time (makespan) while satisfying complex temporal constraints, making it a promising solution for multi-agent planning problems. Copyright © 2025 The Authors.
