N2  - Recent advances in UAV technology have significantly enhanced their deployment in environmental monitoring and resource exploration missions. A key research challenge lies in developing multi-UAV coverage strategies that simultaneously optimize operational performance while strictly satisfying energy and communication constraints. To overcome the challenge, we propose a constrained multi-UAV coverage optimization framework formulated as a Constrained Markov Decision Process and solved via a novel multi-agent reinforcement learning approach. The proposed solution introduces an adaptive constrained optimization mechanism that integrates dynamic sliding-window assessments with Lagrangian multiplier methods, enabling autonomous penalty adjustment through self-tuning multiplier adaptation. Comprehensive simulation experiments demonstrate that our approach achieves significantly better coverage performance while strictly maintaining constraint satisfaction compared to existing approaches. © 2025 IEEE.
