N2  - Cooperation and coordination are highly desired properties of an effective multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) system. Understanding cause-and-effect relationships, know an causal inference, can be exploited to promote the emergence of mutually beneficial behavior in such systems. Inspired by the success of similar work, we demonstrate how causality-based intrinsic rewards can be used to enhance the performance of simple feudal hierarchies for multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL). Our results demonstrate that reinforcing causal influence across levels of hierarchies improves the efficiency of these models and adds support to a causality-first approach to multi-agent reinforcement learning. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd. 2025.
