N2  - This paper designs and implements an underwater target tracking system based on Reinforcement Learning (RL), which combines a user-defined underwater environment model and SAC algorithm to achieve multi-agent cooperation and target tracking. The system simulates the complex motion characteristics of underwater dynamic targets in the virtual environment, including the random motion pattern of the target, the change of depth, the interference of water flow and the limitation of communication range. Through the design of self-defined reward function, the system takes into account the target positioning error and the efficiency of agent behavior, uses recurrent neural network (RNN) to process time series data, and combines experience playback buffer to optimize the training effect. The experimental results show that the system achieves high precision localization of dynamic underwater target with low estimation error of 0. 000 3 under the cooperation of multiple agents, and achieves stable convergence after multiple training. The system has a wide range of potential applications in high real-time application scenarios such as underwater vehicle navigation and marine resource exploration. © 2025 IEEE.
