N2  - Social networking services (SNS) are widely used across national boundaries, and extensive research has been conducted on their applications in marketing as well as the dissemination of emotions and information through such platforms. However, predicting user behavior on SNS remains a significant challenge, underscoring the need for systems capable of modeling and forecasting interaction tendencies. To address this, we have developed an SNS simulation system composed of large language model (LLM)-driven agents. This study investigates the impact of a retrieval-augmented generation mechanism, designed to emulate human-like search behavior, on the quality of generated posts and replies. The experimental results indicate that the proposed mechanism produces the most natural and coherent exchanges among agents. © 2025 IEEE.
