N2  - This study presents a Multi-Agent Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (MADDPG) algorithm for cooperative path planning of UAV swarms in dynamic environments. The algorithm employs a centralized training with decentralized execution framework, enabling effective decision-making among heterogeneous UAVs under partial observability. By formulating the path planning problem as a partially observable Markov decision process (POMDP), we design continuous action spaces that respect UAV kinematic constraints. Simulation results demonstrate that MADDPG significantly enhances task reward acquisition and convergence efficiency compared to traditional multi-agent methods, providing a robust solution for UAV swarm coordination in complex scenarios. © 2025 IEEE.
