N2  - With the advancement of computer science, information wheel and control theory, multi-agent system, as a representative complex system, plays a crucial role in analyzing cluster behavior in various fields such as biology, social science, and military. The multi-agent system possesses the capability to adapt to environmental changes and dynamically adjust its structure for reconfiguration purposes in order to reduce vulnerability and enhance resilience. However, current research is limited to proposing reconfiguration strategies that improve the adaptability and resilience of the system without providing an interpretation of the reconfiguration mechanism and capacity constraints. This paper analyzes the operational mechanism and network structure of a multi-agent system based on the concept of typical operation loop while integrating reconfigurable features to propose a model called reconfigurable heterogeneous multi-agent network (RHMN). Additionally, this study examines network capability constraints under reconfiguration factors by introducing network evaluation indices and resilience measurements based on capability-load. Finally, using missile equipment systems as a case study example, we analyze the resilience of the proposed reconfigurable heterogeneous multi-agent network model using these models and indices to verify their validity and effectiveness. © 2024 IEEE.
