N2  - The modeling and simulation of recycling behavior are becoming more popular for the complexity of recycling systems, while household expired medicines are ignored in this field. Household expired medicines are characterized by low value and high pollution and the difficulty in their recycling lies in how the government improves the behavior of recycling participants. Currently, the modeling of recycling behavior by multiple agents primarily focuses on the end of the recycling participants, with governmental strategies often exhibiting significant subjectivity. This study extends the theoretical framework of household expired medication recycling programs and develops an adaptive multi-agent model for expired medication recycling behavior. This model can simulate both static and dynamic governmental decisions, effectively characterizing changes in resident recycling behavior under various governmental stimuli. Through this model, it is possible to assess the expected effects of different recycling policies. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
