N2  - The multi-agent pursuit problem in complex dynamic environments involves coordinating multiple agents to capture or intercept the evader meanwhile the pursuers need to avoid collisions and adapting to unpredictable environmental changes. We proposed using Safe Reinforcement Learning (Safe RL) to predict the Dynamic Window Approach (DWA) weights, which are then employed for safe local navigation. The improved DWA optimizes agent trajectory planning by considering both velocity constraints and obstacle avoidance, ensuring efficient navigation in dynamic environments. Meanwhile, Safe RL incorporates safety constraints into the learning process, enabling agents to learn optimal policies while minimizing the risk of unsafe behaviors. Our approach allows agents to adapt to dynamic obstacles and shifting environments, making it robust and scalable for real-world applications. Experimental results demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of both pursuit efficiency and safety, outperforming existing techniques in various complex environments. © 2025 Technical Committee on Control Theory, Chinese Association of Automation.
