N2  - Disasters such as earthquakes and tsunamis occur frequently all over the world. Relief activities using swarm intelligent robots have become essential and indispensable. This paper proposes a distributed middleware that can automatically adapt to environmental changes, such as secondary or N-th disasters, sudden obstacles, and network instability, for robots distributed to indoor rescue activities after a disaster. Multiple agents can interact with each other and their environments, and the system is built on a general cloud. The agent controls data messaging, task migration, and duplication to manage key adaptation processes across robots and the cloud, and our adaptation manager controls the agent's lifecycle, which includes creation, relocation, execution, and termination. It enables dynamic reconfiguration of robot behavior in response to changing environmental conditions. In addition, this paper also effectively verifies our examples by implementing three pre-defined policies. Through experimental results, we preliminarily verify the effectiveness of our proposed approach. © 2025 IEEE.
